    public class GermanIDCombinedRecognitionResult
extends BaseRecognitionResult
implements CombinedRecognitionResult
    Represents a result of scanning of both front and back side of German national ID card.

      • isDocumentDataMatch

        public boolean isDocumentDataMatch()
        Returns true if both data on the front side of the document and on the back side of the document match, false otherwise. Address, authority and personal number are written only on back side, while date of issue, place of birth and nationality (full name of country) are written on front side, all other data elements are present on both sides and their values are matched.
        Specified by:
        isDocumentDataMatch in interface CombinedRecognitionResult
        Returns:
        true if both front and back side data match, false otherwise.
